reviews.review:
I got this game (contains Liberation Remastered) for free with AC Odyssey Gold Edition. 

AC III (only focus on main missions and main objects, finished, 17 hours, 38% completion)
story: 6.0/10 (kinda okay)
graphic: 5.0/10 ("remaster" more like HD; little bit dark;)
combat: 4.0/10 (pretty easy, but indicator didn't show even enemy is attacking sometimes)
soundtrack: 5.0/10
game play: 2.5/10
(
 initial key binding for PC is mess; 
 some optional object could be hard and annoying; 
 parkour part can be pretty glitchy;
 switching weapons and tools is wanky;
 traveling through maps is painful that fast travel didn't really help;
 many invisible walls;
 NPC stuck at suspicious state or stuck in place;
 map is designed for console because mouse just didn't work when center isn't there;
 it makes game play so blind and frustration that real life mode didn't contain UI;
 can't interact because of not anonymous;
)
over all: 4.0/10 (this remaster done so little to improve quality of life; only get this game with Odyssey instead of pay alone)


AC III: The Tyranny of King Washington (focus on main missions and main objectives, finished, 4 hours, 61% completion)
episode 1: 4.0/10 (fast travel to mission location is good; but confusion missions and some literally impossible optional objectives are frustrating;)
episode 2: 3.5/10 (switch special powers just like switch tools is painful; more boring and annoying chase sequences; enemies didn't show on mini-map sometimes;)
episode 3: 3.5/10 (grinding side activities to progress main objective; )
over all: 3.5/10 (I'm just glad that I finished the story; dlc is not fun at all)


AC Liberation (focus on main missions, finished, 10 hours, 100% completion)
story: 5/10
graphic: 4/10 (it doesn't look like remastered or HD)
combat: 5/10 (press E but same as AC III, it can be glicthy)
soundtrack: 6/10
game play: 5/10
(
 game provides 3 guises;
 objectives are pretty clear and easy compare to AC III;
 parkour part is great most of time;
 BUT no fast travel so I spend more time on travel than doing mission itself;
 3 guises are really limited in missions;
 path is blocked by bush;
 no damage challenge can be difficult;
)
over all: 5.2/10 (not bad)
